newsitem.title: UK: European gasoline off highs as NYMEX unleaded fall.
newsitem.headline: European gasoline off highs as NYMEX unleaded fall.

text.p: European gasoline trade was thin on Thursday with volatile NYMEX futures keeping prospective arbitrage buyers at bay.
Traders said buyers had initially withdrawn, driven away by early futures-led price gains on the spot market and sharp afternoon NYMEX losses left them sidelined calculating arbitrage profitability.

They said good U.S. demand and stronger crude futures were supporting prices just below morning highs in late trade, but European demand was muted and buying interest for arbitrage had dried up a little.
Eurograde barges talked slightly softer at $221/$223 a tonne fob ARA, with fob cargoes valued around $10 under barges although offers were scarce.
